  "brief": "<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Market Overview</h2>\n\nTech is carrying the load this morning with NASDAQ up 1.40% while old economy sectors get hammered. VIX at 29.33 signals elevated anxiety as Iran conflict disrupts energy markets and supply chains. Pre-market showing clear risk-on rotation into growth names despite macro headwinds.\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> What to Watch</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Netflix Earnings (AMC)</strong> - EPS est 0.78, subscriber growth key after streaming wars intensified</li>\n<li><strong>Jobs Data (8:30 ET)</strong> - Initial claims, continuing claims, and Philly Fed manufacturing all dropping simultaneously</li>\n<li><strong>Iran Developments</strong> - Pakistani mediation showing progress but petrochemical export halt still active</li>\n<li><strong>Energy Disruption</strong> - Fujairah marine fuel sales collapsed, oil price discovery broken according to Reuters</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Sector Rotation</h2>\n\nClassic flight-to-growth pattern with Tech (+1.60%) and Consumer Discretionary (+1.49%) leading while defensive sectors crater. Industrials (-1.25%) and Materials (-1.21%) getting destroyed on war premium fears. Energy paradoxically weak (-0.34%) despite supply disruptions as demand destruction fears dominate.\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-amber\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚡ Key Driver</div>Iran conflict creating dual headwinds: supply chain disruption hitting cyclicals while growth scarcity premium inflates tech multiples</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-red\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚠ Bear Case</div>VIX above 29 with defensive sectors rolling over suggests institutional repositioning for prolonged volatility ahead</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-green\"><div class=\"callout-label\">✦ Bull Case</div>Tech leadership with NASDAQ outperformance by 61bps indicates algorithm buying and momentum continuation potential</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Levels That Matter</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>SPY 700</strong> - Psychological resistance, failure here triggers profit-taking</li>\n<li><strong>QQQ 640</strong> - Key breakout level, hold above confirms tech leadership</li>\n<li><strong>XLI 105</strong> - Industrial sector support, break signals broader cyclical breakdown</li>\n<li><strong>VIX 30</strong> - Fear threshold, breach above accelerates defensive rotation</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr>\n<p><em>Not a prediction. A preparation. Make your plan before the bell.</em></p>"
